# $Header: $

  17 Nov 2015; wjn <wjn@aol.jp> cinnamon-control-center-2.6.0-r1.ebuild:
  gnome-extra/cinnamon{,control-center}: Do not KEYWORD

  09 Nov 2015; wjn <wjn@aol.jp> cinnamon-control-center-2.6.0-r1.ebuild:
  gnome-extra/cinnamon-settings-daemon: Add newly for add IUSE="pulseaudio"

   Change pulseaudio to optional in cinnamon-settings-daemon.

   And also,
  cinnamon[pulseaudio=] and cinnamon-control-center[pulseaudio=] are needed.

  09 Nov 2015; wjn <wjn@aol.jp> cinnamon-control-center-2.6.0-r1.ebuild,
  +files/cinnamon-control-center-disable-pulseaudio.patch:
  Add IUSE="pulseaudio"

   cinnamon-control-center[-pulseaudio] results to omit the sound panel.

   And gnome-extra/cinnamon depends on cinnamon-control-center[pulseaudio=].

  03 Nov 2015; wjn <wjn@aol.jp> cinnamon-control-center-2.6.0-r1.ebuild:
  Fix to drop nm-applet dep when -networkmanager.

*cinnamon-control-center-2.6.0-r1 (02 Nov 2015)

  02 Nov 2015; wjn <wjn@aol.jp> +cinnamon-control-center-2.6.0-r1.ebuild,
  +files/cinnamon-control-center-2.6.0-optional.patch, +metadata.xml:
  Add newly for disabling NetworkManager.

   cinnamon-control-center can be built without NetworkManager (and nm-
  applet).
  NetworkManager has too poor functionality to be forced to install.

